verses.text:
The \nd LORD\nd* your God which goeth before you, he shall
fight for you, according to all that he did for you in Egypt before your
eyes;

Thou shalt sell me meat for money, that I may eat; and give
me water for money, that I may drink: only I will pass through on my
feet;

And we took at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the
Amorites the land that \add was\add* on this side Jordan, from the
river of Arnon unto mount Hermon;

And unto the Reubenites and unto the Gadites I gave from Gilead
even unto the river Arnon half the valley, and the border even unto the
river Jabbok, \add which is\add* the border of the children of Ammon;

But your wives, and your little ones, and your cattle, (\add for\add*
I know that ye have much cattle,) shall abide in your cities which I have
given you;

Only take heed to thyself, and keep thy soul diligently, lest thou
forget the things which thine eyes have seen, and lest they depart
from thy heart all the days of thy life: but teach them thy sons,
and thy sons’ sons;

And because he loved thy fathers, therefore he chose their
seed after them, and brought thee out in his sight with his mighty
power out of Egypt;

And they possessed his land, and the land of Og king of Bashan,
two kings of the Amorites, which \add were\add* on this side Jordan
toward the sunrising;

Know therefore that the \nd LORD\nd* thy God, he \add is\add*
God, the faithful God, which keepeth covenant and mercy with them that
love him and keep his commandments to a thousand generations;

Thou shalt not be afraid of them: \add but\add* shalt well
remember what the \nd LORD\nd* thy God did unto Pharaoh, and unto all
Egypt;

For the \nd LORD\nd* thy God bringeth thee into a good land,
a land of brooks of water, of fountains and depths that spring out
of valleys and hills;

Then thine heart be lifted up, and thou forget the \nd LORD\nd*
thy God, which brought thee forth out of the land of Egypt, from the
house of bondage;

Who fed thee in the wilderness with manna, which thy fathers
knew not, that he might humble thee, and that he might prove thee, to do thee
good at thy latter end;

Thy fathers went down into Egypt with threescore and ten persons;
and now the \nd LORD\nd* thy God hath made thee as the stars of heaven
for multitude.

Therefore shall ye keep all the commandments which I command
you this day, that ye may be strong, and go in and possess the land,
whither ye go to possess it;

¶ For if ye shall diligently keep all these commandments which I
command you, to do them, to love the \nd LORD\nd* your God, to walk
in all his ways, and to cleave unto him;

And the sign or the wonder come to pass, whereof he spake unto thee,
saying, Let us go after other gods, which thou hast not known, and let us
serve them;

\add Namely\add*, of the gods of the people which \add are\add*
round about you, nigh unto thee, or far off from thee, from the \add one\add*
end of the earth even unto the \add other\add* end of the earth;

Then shalt thou enquire, and make search, and ask diligently; and, behold,
\add if it be\add* truth, \add and\add* the thing certain, \add that\add*
such abomination is wrought among you;

For the \nd LORD\nd* thy God blesseth thee, as he promised
thee: and thou shalt lend unto many nations, but thou shalt not borrow;
and thou shalt reign over many nations, but they shall not reign over thee.

¶ And if a Levite come from any of thy gates out of all Israel,
where he sojourned, and come with all the desire of his mind unto the
place which the \nd LORD\nd* shall choose;

¶ The \nd LORD\nd* thy God will raise up unto thee a Prophet
from the midst of thee, of thy brethren, like unto me; unto him ye shall
hearken;

And if the \nd LORD\nd* thy God enlarge thy coast, as he hath
sworn unto thy fathers, and give thee all the land which he promised
to give unto thy fathers;

Then both the men, between whom the controversy \add is\add*,
shall stand before the \nd LORD\nd*, before the priests and the judges,
which shall be in those days;

And the judges shall make diligent inquisition: and, behold,
\add if\add* the witness \add be\add* a false witness, \add and\add*
hath testified falsely against his brother;

And they shall say unto the elders of his city, This our son
\add is\add* stubborn and rebellious, he will not obey our voice;
\add he is\add* a glutton, and a drunkard.

Then the man that lay with her shall give unto the damsel’s
father fifty \add shekels\add* of silver, and she shall be his wife;
because he hath humbled her, he may not put her away all his days.

And it shall be, when thou \add art\add* come in unto the land
which the \nd LORD\nd* thy God giveth  thee \add for\add* an inheritance,
and possessest it, and dwellest therein;

And the \nd LORD\nd* hath avouched thee this day to be his
peculiar people, as he hath promised thee, and that \add thou\add*
shouldest keep all his commandments;

Cursed \add be\add* he that lieth with his father’s wife;
because he uncovereth his father’s skirt. And all the people shall
say, Amen.

If thou wilt not observe to do all the words of this law that are
written in this book, that thou mayest fear this glorious and fearful
name, THE \nd LORD\nd* THY GOD;

¶ And Moses called unto all Israel, and said unto them, Ye have
seen all that the \nd LORD\nd* did before your eyes in the land of
Egypt unto Pharaoh, and unto all his servants, and unto all his land;

And shalt return unto the \nd LORD\nd* thy God, and shalt obey
his voice according to all that I command thee this day, thou and thy
children, with all thine heart, and with all thy soul;

For I know thy rebellion, and thy stiff neck: behold, while I am yet
alive with you this day, ye have been rebellious against the \nd LORD\nd*;
and how much more after my death?

He found him in a desert land, and in the waste howling wilderness;
he led him about, he instructed him, he kept him as the apple of his
eye.\f + \fr 32.10  \ft led: or, compassed\f*

He made him ride on the high places of the earth, that he might
eat the increase of the fields; and he made him to suck honey out of the
rock, and oil out of the flinty rock;

And he said, I will hide my face from them, I will see what their
end \add shall be:\add* for they \add are\add* a very froward generation,
children in whom \add is\add* no faith.

¶ And of Levi he said, \add Let\add* thy Thummim and thy Urim
\add be\add* with thy holy one, whom thou didst prove at Massah,
\add and with\add* whom thou didst strive at the waters of Meribah;

¶ And Joshua the son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom;
for Moses had laid his hands upon him: and the children of Israel
hearkened  unto him, and did as the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses.
